content:
To populate datasets with data from data sources, you can import the data directly from the source or extract and prepare it before loading into a dataset.

Import Data

You can import data from Excel spreadsheets (via a connector) and CSV files directly into a dataset. This approach populates the dataset without modifying the data.

Prepare and Load Data

If you want to make any changes to the data, you can use recipes and dataflows. Recipes and dataflows are powerful features that you can use to cleanse, prepare, and optimize your data for analysis.

You can also get started with data integration or consider other ways to integrate data.
title: Ways to Get Data into Datasets
